ecount it because they forgot how much it was), put the coin purse away, then follow this procedure again for their wallet.  Then once they've put their wallet away, they take the receipt, have to look for their wallets again (gee, it's been a long two minutes since they put it away), and stick their receipts in their wallet.<br><br>That's more towards the extreme, but it wouldn't take me too many people like that before I'd just be throwing the money at the people and screaming &quot;GTF out of my store before I kick your simple little A$$ you stupid MF&quot;.  (I do wonder sometimes why I don't work in a customer relations position).  Anyways, I'm sure that's why they give it all to you at once, it's more convenient for them.<br><br>As far as the bag, I've seen things both ways.  I'll stop to get gas driving with my kids (leaving them in the car), and I'll buy two sodas, a bag of chips, and a couple candy items.  The cashier will ring me up, and say have a nice day, with everything lying on the counter.  Common sense would dictate that with more then 1 item they should get bagged.  As far as a bag for a single item, bags are generally easier to handle for carrying stuff (who knows, I might be stopping at another store or three before I go home). <br><br>Now Vae, we are out to get.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwuchild.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WuChild</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/20/02 1:53:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><