 you from a promotion for like 6 months.<br><br>Came in the next day with a stern letter regarding my retirement... they were like &quot;but where are you going to work?! where will you go?!&quot; Like a job stacking apples and milk is the best job on the planet.... yes the pay was nice 12$ an hour with killer benefits, but it's also a kind of trap, as many 50 year-old checkers will tell you. Yes people work for 30+ years &quot;handing change&quot; back to idiots. So I left that sh|t job and got my ass back in school.<br><br>In that time at the grocery store, I took away ONE thing... how to be a customer who GETS WHAT THEY WANT. I can sweet talk a free month of DSL out of my isp, yep have done it. I've cashed 2 party checks in places where you can't BUY anything with a check.<br><br>One thing to remember as a professional customer... make your face known, make them regard you as a regular. Tip well at your fav restaurant, smile at people, use whatever charm you have... and you will get whatever you want... being a customer is a partnership, they make money, you come back and get treated well. It has to start on the customers end tho, and pick your battles.<br><br>That is all <p><a target="new" href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=9779>Maui's stuff</a> <BR> <a target="new" href=http://maui.freewebspace.com/photo.html>Maui himself</a</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ugregar1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gregar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/21/02 10:31:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   OOC Rant: Cashiers</span><hr size=1> Actually, Wolfy, I spoke to all of them, and they are indeed out to get YOU! <!--EZCODE EMO