d part-time at Software Etc during the holidays, we were taught not only to hand the cash back on top of the change, but to actually count out the sale. &quot;$10.95 out of $15.00, your change is $4.05...  5 cents is 11, 12, 13, 14 and 15, have a nice evening!&quot;<br>I rarely encounter this anymore, which sucks cause it's so handy. /cheer Savok!<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I agree with Wu....I was a cashier for 2 years and let me tell you, customers are by far worse than cashiers. They are not always right, most of the time they are morons. I am never working in customer service again. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->When you take my money, I am always right. When I take your money, you are always right.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I am one of those manager types for Circuit City<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The problem I see everyday is people buying a single video cassette with a freaking 100 bill because there to cool to have anything less then a Benjamin in there wallet when they leave the house. I'm not a money laundering service pal, you WILL give me one of those 5 spots I saw tucked underneath that 100 or your not getting this tape! <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Uhm, yes, I'll get my tape... at Best Buy.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Nothing comes close though to my hatred of the damn people who insist on writing checks. I'm sorry, but its common knowledge that you do NOT buy a digital camcorder with a check. I'm going to need a blood sample, retinal scan, thumbprint, a catalog of your hair index, boy scout retirement id, and a written note from your deceased grandmother before I let you write a check for a 1,500 dollar item that you bought because 'it looks fat!'.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It looks &quot;p.h.a.t&quot; actually. I dunno about buying a digital camcorder with a check, but I will buy a big-screen tv worth twice the camcorder with a check. Yup, Best Buy again. I'm not a big advocate of Best Buy, but they seem to realise that I don't have to shop there.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> One thing to remember as a professional customer... make your face known, make them regard you as a regular. Tip well at your fav restaurant, smile at people, use whatever charm you have...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This is a very good tip and very true. The waitresses at the Sonic drive in rush to get my order to me because I tip well, I can control which driver brings my pizza by how I tip, and by tipping well I can pretty much count on getting it fast and hot. Also, if your face is known as a regular, and you have a problem with a product, you'll get a lot farther toward getting it resolved, faster. <br><br>I usually get along okay with cashiers, because of the above policy, but I hate grocery stores, and Wal-mart in particular, because they have 35 checkout lanes and 3 cashiers working. One manager type said it was because they had trouble getting the cashiers to come in... well how bout some incentive then? You can't have good employees on the cheap, not for long.<br>And my #1 with a bullet absolute top peeve about grocery stores is the newfangled <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> plastic bags</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> What moron came up with this?? Half the time you can only get 1 item in a bag, they're so small. There's always one that splits open because the clerk overfilled it, they have no strength to them so your food spreads out all over the trunk or back seat, they make lousy garbage bags, take 3 times as many loads to get in the house as the old fashioned paper bags, and I suspect they're less bio-degradable than the old paper bags. Oh, and they always always always squash the bread products! You stick a loaf of bread in one of those little plastic bags and it's gonna get squished unless you grab a handle in each hand and carry it with your arms apart.<br><br>Oops.. sorry to go on.. I forgot I'm on /ignore. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p>Aldrin of the Nexus<BR><a href="http://www.xtimports.com/index.html"><img src="http://www.xtimports.com/data/Everquest/pics/Aldrinsig2.jpg" alt="Extra Terrestrial Imports " align="left" border="0" hspace="0" width="240" height="263"></a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showMessageRange?topicID=362.topic&start=21&stop=25>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=362.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=362.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=362.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/AddReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=362.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.threadControl?topicID=362.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=362.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukser